f their"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_iEoraAs", "text_ar": "اـِعْرَاس"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aEoraAs", "text_ar": "اَعْرَاس"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[thus differently written in different MSS.]; (S, A, O, Msb, K;) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "when the one goes in to the other:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(IAth:) you say"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rajulN", "text_ar": "رَجُلٌ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaruwsN", "text_ar": "عَرُوسٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a bridegroom,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "vulgarly, in the present day, ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eariys", "text_ar": "عَرِيس", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",] and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AimoraA^apN EaruwsN", "text_ar": "اِمْرَاَةٌ عَرُوسٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a bride,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "vulgarly, in the present day, ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Earuwsap", "text_ar": "عَرُوسَة", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (S:) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EuruwsN", "text_ar": "عُرُوسٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is a dial. var. of the same: (IAar, TA:) pl. mase."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EurusN", "text_ar": "عُرُسٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, O, Msb, K) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aEoraAsN", "text_ar": "اَعْرَاسٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (TA;) and pl. fem."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaraAy^isu", "text_ar": "عَرَايِسُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (S, O, Msb, K.) [See"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Earisa", "text_ar": "عَرِسَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in two places.] It is said in a prov.,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kaAda AlEaruwsu", "text_ar": "كَادَ العَرُوسُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yakuwnu A^amiyrFA", "text_ar": "يَكُونُ اَمِيرًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The bridegroom was near to being a prince"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (S: in the O,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "malikFA", "text_ar": "مَلِكًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".) The dim. is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Euray~isN", "text_ar": "عُرَيِّسٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", without the addition of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "p", "text_ar": "ة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "to distinguish the fem., because of the fourth letter. (TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aboyaAtN EaraAy^isu", "text_ar": "اَبْيَاتٌ عَرَايِسُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Verses of which the words are marked with diacritical points:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "for, as Esh-Shereeshee says, the Arabs used to adorn the bride by speckling her cheeks with saffron: opposed to"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aboyaAtN EawaATilu", "text_ar": "اَبْيَاتٌ عَوَاطِلُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (Har p. 610.) ―         -b3-  [Hence also,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaraAy^isu AlA_ibili", "text_ar": "عَرَايِسُ الاـِبِلِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The high-bred of camels."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A.)"}], "source_refs": ["IAth", "S", "IAar", "TA", "O", "Msb", "K"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}